    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> The method was checking if the component was collapsed or not\n> before triggering the render\n\nSome websites are using collapsing widgets to be able to have a lot of widgets without messing up the display. Thus always rendering widgets was not efficient since a lot of them were collapsed.\n\n> As we now always need to update the\n> render of the header, being collapsed or not\n\nWe only need to update it when the active count has changed right? We should find a way to not render the widget if no values were updated. Unsure that's doable.\n",
    "created_at": "2016-06-06T09:45:02Z",
